  title: Do you need to use the [Flags] attribute to use bitwise operations on enums?
  text: Technically, no. You can use bitwise operations without the [Flags] attribute.
    However, using [Flags] improves code readability by making it so that if you
    convert the enum to a string you get a list of enabled flags with their names
    instead of a numeric value.
